<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000037#     2#          915#">Va. Code Ann. § 37.2-915</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_37.2-915"/><heading><desig>§ 37.2-915.</desig><title>Representation of Commonwealth and person subject to commitment; nature of proceedings</title></heading><bodyText><p>The Attorney General shall represent the Commonwealth in all proceedings held pursuant to this chapter. The Attorney General shall receive prior written notice of all proceedings held under this chapter in which he is to represent the Commonwealth.</p><p>The court shall appoint counsel for the person subject to commitment or conditional release pursuant to subsection C of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 37.2-906"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 37.2-906">§ 37.2-906<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000037#     2#          906#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> unless the person waives his right to counsel. The court shall consider appointment of the person who represented the person in previous proceedings.</p><p>All proceedings held under this chapter shall be civil proceedings.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="1999 VA CH 946"><content><span normalizedCite="1999 Va. Ch. 946">1999, cc. 946<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#1999#0009